    {
      "text": "2008 video game for the Nintendo DS",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikidata"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ninja Gaiden: Dragon Sword (ニンジャガイデン ドラゴンソード, Ninja Gaiden Doragon Sōdo) is a 2008 action-adventure game developed by Team Ninja and published by Tecmo and Ubisoft for the Nintendo DS. A main installment in the Ninja Gaiden series, it features Ryu Hayabusa as the protagonist. The game is the first portable video game title in the series to be developed by Team Ninja and the first game developed by this company to be released for the Nintendo system. Dragon Sword is set between Ninja Gaiden and Ninja Gaiden II.\nThis title is presented in a third person, pseudo-3D manner, meaning all the game-models are rendered in full 3D, but the world the player travels around in is pre-rendered. When played, the Nintendo DS is held sideways, as in Hotel Dusk: Room 215 and Brain Age: Train Your Brain in Minutes a Day!. The left screen shows the area map, while the right displays the main gameplay, when set for right-handed play, and reverse when set for left-handed play.\nSet six months after Ninja Gaiden, Ryu Hayabusa has rebuilt the Hayabusa Village. When fellow villager and kunoichi, Momiji, is kidnapped by the Black Spider Ninja Clan, he is forced to find her, while uncovering the secrets behin",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "『NINJA GAIDEN Dragon Sword』（ニンジャガイデン ドラゴンソード）は、Team NINJAが開発して、テクモが2008年3月20日に発売したニンテンドーDS用のアクションアドベンチャーゲーム。通称「ニンジャガDS」。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "wikipedia_ja"
    },
    {
      "text": "《忍者外傳 龍劍》（日语：ニンジャガイデン ドラゴンソード，英语：Ninja Gaiden: Dragon Sword，中国大陆译作“忍者龙剑传 龙剑”，香港和台湾译作“忍者外傳 龍劍”）是一款由Team Ninja開發并由特库摩發售在任天堂DS平台上的動作遊戲。本作是第一款由Team Ninja团队开发的掌机作品，也是忍者外傳系列继《忍者龙剑传GB：摩天楼决战》后第二款登陆任天堂掌机平台的作品。\n《忍者外傳 龍劍》于2008年3月20日于日本发售、2008年3月25日在北美发售、2008年6月27日在欧洲地区发售。截止2009年2月，本作在全球已销售34万余套。",
      "lang": "zh",
      "source": "wikipedia_zh"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ninja Gaiden: Dragon Sword est un jeu vidéo d'action-aventure édité par Tecmo et développé par la Team Ninja. Il est distribué en 2008 sur Nintendo DS.",
      "lang": "fr",
      "source": "wikipedia_fr"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ninja Gaiden Dragon Sword è un videogioco di tipo avventura dinamica, parte della serie Ninja Gaiden, sviluppato dal Team Ninja e pubblicato da Tecmo e Ubisoft nel 2008 per Nintendo DS.",
      "lang": "it",
      "source": "wikipedia_it"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ninja Gaiden: Dragon Sword — видеоигра жанра action-adventure, разработанная японской компанией Team Ninja и выпущенная в 2008 году для портативной консоли Nintendo DS. Является частью серии Ninja Gaiden; её действие происходит между событиями игры 2004 года и её сиквела.",
      "lang": "ru",
      "source": "wikipedia_ru"
    }
  ]
